cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.ET, cs.SE, cs.RO

The paper discusses the application of weakest precondition semantics to analyze a purely quantum language fragment, which falls under the category of program verification and logic (cs.LO). The paper also extends proof rules for classical probabilistic programs to purely quantum programs, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper deals with the quantum part of a potential quantum computer, which falls under the category of emerging technologies (cs.ET). The paper introduces denotational semantics, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses reasoning about quantum loops, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO).
